data.Name: Attack Attack!
data.Bio: Attack Attack! are an American electronicore band from Westerville, Ohio, formed in 2005. Attack Attack!'s first release, an independent EP titled If Guns Are Outlawed, Can We Use Swords?, was released in 2008, which led to the signing of the band to Rise Records the same year. They then released their two full-length albums, Someday Came Suddenly and a self-titled album (Attack Attack!) both through Rise. A third album entitled This Means War was released on January 17, 2012, also through Rise. The band is currently unsigned. Read more on Last.fm

data.Name: Electric Callboy
data.Bio: Electric Callboy (formerly known as Eskimo Callboy) is a German metalcore/electronicore band formed in Castrop-Rauxel in 2010. The band consists of former lead singer of To the Rats and WolvesNico Sallach, who replaced longtime lead singer Sebastian "Sushi" Biesler who left the band in early 2020.
